Welcome to Seattle Walking Tour
description:
This is a fun, informative tour that's easy to walk, but covers a lot of ground. We will point out the big iconic sites, but visit a few places off the beaten path as well.
In this tour we’ll get you acquainted with Seattle. Starting in the Pioneer Square neighborhood, you’ll learn about the history and founding of the emerald city. We'll visit the cities art district, Chinatown-international district and meander through the downtown core. Then it’s a ride through the future past on the historic monorail, which we’ll ride to Seattle Center, the site of the 1962 world’s fair. 
This is a walking tour and we cover roughly 2.5 miles on foot. The tour will take place no matter the weather, rain or shine, (we only cancel during weather advisories). We recommend you dress appropriately, including footwear.

review.name: Highly recommend.
review.reviewBody: James was an amazing tour guide. Excellent tour to see so much of Seattle. Lots of walking, which I love!  Highly recommend.

review.name: Exceptional tour
review.reviewBody:
James is an exceptional tour guide and a very
likable human being. He is knowledgeable.
flexible, interesting, and helpful. Within the
span of a few hours, my friends and I learned
a tremendous amount about the beautiful
city of Seattle and had a great time. I highly
recommend James' walking tours to all
visitors to Seattle.

review.name: so glad we took this tour
review.reviewBody: on a first-time visit to seattle with some dear old friends, this tour was a surprising highlight -- it felt easy, eye-opening, informative and fun, and best of all like it was guided by yet another friend. james was smart, kind and just a cool person to spend the morning with, and by the end of our tour we felt we had seen some of the best spots and given a warm welcome to a truly beautiful city.

review.name: Informative and fun
review.reviewBody: Great tour, James knows his stuff and was friendly and entertaining too. A fun and non-strenuous way to see and understand some parts of the city you might otherwise not visit.

review.name: Highly recommend! Fantastic way to hear the history & see so many different parts of downtown Seattle.
review.reviewBody: This was a wonderful way to see the downtown region of Seattle & James gave us a knowledgeable insight into the local area & its history. We were able to see highlights and beautiful buildings in the area. Wear your walking shoes. Highly recommend to anyone visiting Seattle.

review.name: Brilliant tour - would highly recommend !
review.reviewBody: James our guide was brilliant - very knowledgeable and we learnt and saw so much about Seattle that  we would never have seen or known. Can highly recommend this tour thanks.

review.name: Take a Seattle walking tour
review.reviewBody: We always love city walking tours. This tour was no exception. James was our guide. He has extensive knowledge of the city past and present. So we were able to see and learn things about Seattle that we would not have on our own. The pace is comfortable. Questions were encouraged. And James was fully engaged with us. Highly recommend!

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: We chose this tour for our first day in Seattle to get a nice overview of the city to make the most of our 3 days here. Our guide James is both knowledgeable and passionate about Seattle. The tour covered many of the city's high points and James was able to provide really great information at each stop. As a Seattle resident, he was able to provide nice recommendations for shopping and eating. Highly recommended!

review.name: Great way to see the ciry
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide was terrific and thoughtful (he knew when to offer toilets and made an effort to address the unhoused and ensure we were respectful). We loved his knowledge, as well as his choices - especially the library. This was a great way to get a feel for the city and highlights.

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: We learned a lot of Seattle history, covered multiple neighborhoods, and several of the places we visited I wouldn’t have thought to go to on my own but were definitely worth seeing, like the library. Highly recommend.

name: Modern luxury with sunset views of the Puget Sound in historic Queen Anne
description:
Spectacular sunset views from deck, living room and master bedrooms of this spacious 3 bedroom 2600 sqft house is the perfect retreat for your group. Its convenient proximity to various tourist attractions in the City and major employers in the area (Amazon, Google, Facebook - to name a few) will make this house perfect for leisure and business travelers alike. The house has an attached 2-car garage for you to securely park your cars, and has space for two more cars on the driveway. On the other hand, with a walk score of 65 and right across the street from Bus Route #1 that can take you to the downtown in minutes, you might not need a car, after all.

Some Points of Interest conveniently close to the house:
- Kinnear Park has spectacular views of West Seattle, Magnolia and all the way out into Elliott Bay is 0.4 miles away. 
- Kerry Park is popular with photographers who want to capture the skyline of Seattle and is only 0.7 miles away. 
- Space Needle, Museum of Pop Culture, Chihuly Garden and Glass, Seattle Center, Monorail, "Ride the Ducks"  are all 1.6 miles away and are accessible by public transport one block from the house. 
- Pike Place Market and the aquarium are about 2.3 miles away
